                    </span>
                </span> <a href="/3028-12" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Sex: </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Julian</span> was male. <a href="/3028-13" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><h4>Occupation(s): </h4><p class="indent"><span class="tei-persName">Julian</span> was Bishop of <span class="tei-placeName"> Emesa </span>.  <a href="/3028-14" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p></div><div class="sources"><h3>Events</h3><p class="indent">Severus
                            defended his ordination practices by pointing out that many other godly
                            bishops approved, including Julian, who allowed
                                Severus to
                            ordain the deacon Irenaeus, and Dionysius, who
                            allowed Severus
                            to ordain the deacon Anatolius.  <a href="/3028-62" class="factoid-more">See factoid page
                        <span class="glyphicon glyphicon-circle-arrow-right" aria-hidden="true"/></a></p><hr/></div><div class="citation"><h3>How to cite:</h3><span class="element">
